laboratory_examinations.findings: The liver echotexture is normal. There are no focal hepatic lesions. The gallbladder is mildly distended with several multiple stones visible. The patient has a positive sonographic Murphy's sign. There is no overt gallbladder wall thickening or pericholecystic fluid. The common bile duct measures 5-7 mm, which is top normal. There is no intra- or extra-hepatic biliary dilatation. The spleen is mildly enlarged at 13 cm. The main portal vein is patent.
